  "prompt": "How often should one visit a dentist?",
  "response": "Generally, it is recommended that adults visit a dentist every 6 months (twice a year) for routine checkups and professional cleaning. However, the specific frequency can depend on individual factors such as:\n\n1. Overall oral health\n2. Age\n3. Risk factors for dental problems\n4. Existing medical conditions\n5. Oral hygiene habits\n\nSome people might need more frequent visits, such as:\n- Those with a history of gum disease\n- People with diabetes\n- Smokers\n- Individuals with weak immune systems\n- Pregnant women\n\nChildren and teenagers may also need more frequent dental visits as their teeth are developing.\n\nAlways consult with your dentist to determine the most appropriate checkup schedule for your specific needs.",
